For the IAS (Insert as Select) statement, only the select part is parallelized, while the insert itself is done serially. A way to see that is by examining the execution plan, specifically the location of the â€œLoad as Selectâ€ step.
In the IAS execution plan it is above the â€œPX Coordinatorâ€ Step, while for the CTAS (Create Table as Select) case it is below the â€œPX Coordinatorâ€ step.
A common reason for this behavior is if parallel DML is not enabled, which seems to be your case (from the sql monitor report -> <param name="parallel_dml_mode">disabled</param>).
You can enable parallel dml for the session using : ALTER SESSION ENABLE PARALLEL DML
